WEBVTT

00:00:02.780 --> 00:00:08.360
There's always the custom that when a person is about to die, they first make a wish and then they bury them.

00:00:09.940 --> 00:00:18.140
There was a person who used a wheelchair and when he was about to die, with all his family around his bed, he made his wish.

00:00:18.120 --> 00:00:21.320
When I die, I want them to put it inside the coffin.

00:00:23.760 --> 00:00:30.466
And the family granted his wish, and the day of the funeral arrived, and the family buried him with his wheelchair.

00:00:31.420 --> 00:00:37.100
The second person was blind, and when he was about to die, with all his family around his bed, he made his wish.

00:00:37.080 --> 00:00:46.326
I want that when I die, please, and the family granted it. When he died, at the funeral they buried the blind person and placed his cane inside the coffin.

00:00:47.620 --> 00:00:53.700
And the third was an oral deaf person, and when he was about to die with all his family he made his wish.

00:00:53.220 --> 00:00:59.983
I wish, and his family granted it. When they buried him, they put the cochlear implant and the hearing aid inside the coffin.

00:01:01.340 --> 00:01:06.620
Then came a signing deaf person, and when he was about to die, he made his wish, and they granted it.

00:01:06.720 --> 00:01:13.120
When the burial was held, they brought the live interpreter in handcuffs and buried her with the deaf person.
